//Grid system basically divides whole web pages into twelve equivalent parts.It's very helpful in arranging pictures equidistant and properly.

For eg:

<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>
			<div class="col-lg-1 pink">COL LG 1</div>

		</div>
This will show 12 coloumns equidistand and equivalent to each other on a webpage.

In the grid system there are total 12 units.When we alot a coloum to 3 unit by col-lg-3 and there are 4 coloumn there will be 4 coloumn showing in a line because each coloumn will take 3 units and total will be 12units. And if we set col-lg-4 then there will be 3 coloumns in the line (row) and the remaining one will be below the first.
There's a thing called nested grid in which first we devide a line(12 units) into 4 coloumns and now we can also divide those 1 coloumns into 12 units using nested grid.
here's the code:
<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
		 <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 pink">
		 	<div class="row">
           <div class="col-lg-6 orange">First Half</div>
           <div class="col-lg-6 orange">Other Half</div>
		  </div>
		 </div>
		 <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 pink">COL LG 1</div>
		 <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 pink">COL LG 1</div>
		 <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 pink">
		 	<div class="row">          //Dividing the last coloumn into different parts and assigning each units as 2.So there will be total 6 equal parts.
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">1</div>
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">2</div>
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">3</div>
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">4</div>
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">5</div>
		 	<div class="col-lg-2 blue">6</div>
		 </div>

		</div>
		
        </div>
	</div>

